column5: Hi all,  Got out late afternoon on a lake that holds lakers and walleye. Lots and lots of small lakers and lots of chunky walleye. First time I have ever fished walleye in 5 feet of water on the ice.
No seriously, it was really fun.....lol.
Lol.  Looks like another epic day! You sure have come along way as an angler since I first seen ya post here Simon!

Simon, you gotta quit flipping fish outta the hole lol.  Darn I wanted to see that bigger trout! All the eyes were chunky, great fish!  I just rewatched this since the kids are gone and I could cast it on the tele, way better than on my phone lol
Vid's like that make me want to move.  However I cannot be to far from my kids.  Fishing is good here but almost never that good in a short time.

But all in one day is how I read it Simon, even with editing
